> What a catch! This Mediterranean-style combination of fresh, bright flavors piled atop a mild, flaky, and tender barramundi fillet makes a light and quick dinner idea. Pan-seared barramundi is butter-basted for a deliciously browned crust and juicy finish. It's then topped with a bright and briny tomato-feta salad with lemon and scallions and served with garlicky roasted green beans and fluffy scallion rice. Don't let this one get away!

== Roasted Green Beans ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry
@green beans{6%ounce}.

Trim green beans if necessary. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating
whites from greens. Dice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch pieces. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon},
half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest later), @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

== Scallion Rice ==

While green beans roast, in a #small pot{} (medium pot for 4 servings),
combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, scallion whites, @seafood stock concentrate{1},
¾ cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4), and a pinch of salt; bring to a boil. Once
boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Buttery Barramundi ==

Once rice has cooked about 8 minutes, pat @barramundi{10%ounce} dry with
#paper towels{}; season all over with remaining garlic powder, salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{}, preferably
nonstick, over medium-high heat. Add barramundi, skin sides down, to pan. Cook
until skin is crispy, ~{4-5%minutes}. Flip and cook until fish is cooked
through, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

In the last minute of cooking, add @butter{1/2%tablespoon} (1 TBSP for 4
servings) and gently baste barramundi with melted butter.

Remove pan from heat and set aside until ready to serve.

== Tomato-Feta Salad ==

While barramundi cooks, in a #medium bowl{}, combine tomato, scallion greens,
@feta cheese{1/2%cup}, @olive oil{2%teaspoon} (4 tsp for 4 servings), juice from
one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4), and as much lemon zest as you like. Taste
and season with salt and pepper if needed.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a #fork{}.

Divide rice, barramundi, and green beans between plates in separate sections.
Spoon any remaining butter from pan over barramundi; top with tomato salad.
Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

> Barramundi is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.